<p class="c0"><span class="c7 c9"></span></p>
<p class="c6"><span class="c2">Her expression has shifted significantly. &nbsp;You believe she is concerned. &nbsp;Ah, of course. &nbsp;You hadn&rsquo;t fully considered the potential harm such a claim could cause if taken at face value. &nbsp;While it bears little sense after due consideration, beforehand it would imply that there are potentially enemies capable of hiding anywhere, even among the populace. &nbsp;While this is true regardless, it would not do well to put it at the forefront of the people&rsquo;s minds, especially not when they are already strained from want.</span></p>
<p class="c3"><span class="c7 c9">&ldquo;I understand your concern, Ledret. &nbsp;However, I think their claim is unlikely. &nbsp;Even if there is such an entity, their behaviour would lend more to them being some other form of shape shifter, some abomination, fey, or outsider. &nbsp;I have been meaning to discuss with The First regarding potential-&rdquo;</span></p>
